As Public Safety Power Shutoffs impact residents across California, a non-emergency hotline has been established to help medically vulnerable Californians & health & community care facilities find resources in their communities during shutoffs. Hotline: (833) 284-3473

4/4 -Keep mobile phones and other necessary devices charged. My office will relay updates as we receive them. For the most recent information from PG&E on this public safety power shutoff please visit: https://www.pge.com/en_US/safety/emergency-preparedness/natural-disaster/wildfires/public-safety-event.page

3/4 -Have an emergency kit with enough non-perishable food to last your household a week, flashlights and spare batteries available as well as battery powered or crank radios. Keep cash on hand and a full tank of gas as ATM’s and gas pumps could be out of commission.

Confirm or update your contact information with PG&E to receive updates at the link below. https://www.pge.com/en_US/residential/your-account/account-management/manage-your-account/alerts-and-notifications/update-your-contact-information.page
